# Proto-Generated Files

## Never Manually Edit Generated Artifacts

The following files are **generated artifacts** — never edit them directly:

| File pattern | Generated by |
|---|---|
| `*.pb.go`, `*.pb.gw.go` | `make proto-gen` |
| `client/docs/swagger-ui/swagger.json` | `make proto-swagger-gen` |

Manual edits will be silently overwritten on the next `make` run.

## Workflow for Proto Changes

When any `.proto` file is modified:

1. Edit `.proto` files in `proto/`.
2. Run `make proto-gen` to regenerate `*.pb.go` / `*.pb.gw.go`.
3. Update any affected Go code (keeper, handlers, tests) that consumes the changed types.
4. Commit all generated diffs together with the proto and Go changes — they are expected output, not manual edits.

## Acceptance

- Diffs in generated files produced by make targets are deterministic and correct; treat them as expected output.
- If a proto was modified, the corresponding generated file diffs are required and must be included in the same commit.
